external_knowledge:
- 'top three' refers to the content items with the highest number of views per creator;
- 'published items' indicate that only the content with `is_published` set to 1 is considered;
- 'creator' is synonymous with 'user_id' in the database schema.

- 'names' refers to both username and personal names (first and last name);
- 'roles' refers to the user's role in the system (admin, moderator, etc.);
- 'contact information' includes email, phone number, and social media links;
- 'personal biography' also includes the location and profile picture URL;
- 'recent activities' cover the last visit date and IP address;
- 'account status' includes active status and failed login attempts;
- 'lockout expiration' indicates when the account will be unlocked after multiple failed login attempts;

- "beacon bearers" metaphorically refers to content creators;
- "content forest" represents the collection of content created by users;
- "shining stars" metaphorically describes the most viewed content items;
- "luminosity levels" refer to the views count of the content items.

sql:
SELECT user_name, last_visit, last_ip
FROM users
WHERE created_at = (SELECT MAX(created_at) FROM users);

SELECT user_id, credit_type, SUM(credit_amount) AS total_credits
FROM credits
GROUP BY user_id, credit_type;

SELECT user_id, activity_type, activity_date 
FROM user_activity 
ORDER BY user_id;

SELECT users.user_name, content.title
FROM users
INNER JOIN content ON users.user_id = content.creator_id;

SELECT user_id, user_name, email, last_visit, last_ip
FROM users
WHERE is_active = 1 AND failed_login_attempts > 5;

SELECT * FROM credits
WHERE user_id IN (
  SELECT user_id FROM users
  WHERE failed_login_attempts > 5
);
